4.4.1 Supported registries
--------------------------

The following values of ‘type’ are supported:

   • ‘melpa’ — the ‘recipes/’ directory of MELPA
     (https://github.com/melpa/melpa) or a fork; contains MELPA-style
     recipe files.
   • ‘elpa’ — the ‘elpa-packages’ file of GNU ELPA
     (https://git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/emacs/elpa.git/) or NonGNU ELPA
     (https://git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/emacs/nongnu.git/).
   • ‘archive-contents’ — a pre-built package archive as supported by
     ‘package.el’ (e.g.  an ‘archive-contents’ file).  This is an
     _impure_ registry; see below.
   • ‘gitmodules’ — the ‘.gitmodules’ list of emacsmirror/epkgs
     (https://github.com/emacsmirror/epkgs).

   A fifth type, ‘archive’, also exists but is on track to be removed
upstream and should not be used in new configurations.

   _Impure_ registries (‘archive-contents’) require Nix to make a
network connection.  The user must pass ‘--impure’ when running the lock
operation.  All other registry types are _pure_: they are tracked as Nix
flake inputs and locked to particular revisions.

   Once all packages in a configuration are locked, the user can build
the configuration without ‘--impure’, which means the entire
configuration is pure.  Every time the user adds a new package, the lock
operation must be re-run.


File: emacs-twist.info,  Node: MELPA (pure),  Next: ELPA (pure),  Prev: Supported registries,  Up: Registry Configuration

4.4.2 MELPA (pure)
------------------

Use a flake input pointing to the MELPA repository (or a fork) with
‘flake = false’, then reference its ‘recipes/’ directory:

     # In flake inputs:
     melpa = {
       url = "github:melpa/melpa";
       flake = false;
     };

     # In registries:
     {
       name = "melpa";
       type = "melpa";
       path = inputs.melpa.outPath + "/recipes";
     }


File: emacs-twist.info,  Node: ELPA (pure),  Next: Emacsmirror (pure),  Prev: MELPA (pure),  Up: Registry Configuration

4.4.3 ELPA (pure)
-----------------

Use a flake input pointing to the GNU ELPA or NonGNU ELPA repository,
then reference the ‘elpa-packages’ file.  For GNU ELPA, you should also
supply ‘core-src’ (the Emacs source tree) so that Core ELPA packages can
be built from source, and set ‘auto-sync-only = true’ to skip packages
that cannot be built from source:

     # Recommended configuration for GNU ELPA:
     {
       type = "elpa";
       path = inputs.gnu-elpa.outPath + "/elpa-packages";
       core-src = pkgs.emacs.src;
       auto-sync-only = true;
     }

     # NonGNU ELPA (no core-src needed):
     {
       type = "elpa";
       path = inputs.nongnu.outPath + "/elpa-packages";
     }


File: emacs-twist.info,  Node: Emacsmirror (pure),  Next: Package archives (impure),  Prev: ELPA (pure),  Up: Registry Configuration

4.4.4 Emacsmirror (pure)
------------------------

Emacsmirror tracks almost every Emacs Lisp package ever published.  Use
its ‘.gitmodules’ file:

     # In flake inputs:
     epkgs = {
       url = "github:emacsmirror/epkgs";
       flake = false;
     };

     # In registries:
     {
       name = "emacsmirror";
       type = "gitmodules";
       path = inputs.epkgs.outPath + "/.gitmodules";
     }


File: emacs-twist.info,  Node: Package archives (impure),  Next: Registry entry fields,  Prev: Emacsmirror (pure),  Up: Registry Configuration

4.4.5 Package archives (impure)
-------------------------------

An ‘archive-contents’ registry points to a pre-built archive.  Because
Nix must download the archive-contents file at evaluation time, this
requires ‘--impure’:

     {
       name = "gnu";
       type = "archive-contents";
       path = inputs.gnu-elpa-archive.outPath;
       base-url = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/d12frosted/elpa-mirror/master/gnu/";
     }

   Using a mirror (as in the example above) avoids relying on the live
GNU ELPA server.


File: emacs-twist.info,  Node: Registry entry fields,  Prev: Package archives (impure),  Up: Registry Configuration

4.4.6 Registry entry fields
---------------------------

Field              Applies to                   Description
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
‘type’             all                          Registry type (required): ‘melpa’, ‘elpa’, ‘archive-contents’, ‘gitmodules’
‘name’             all                          Optional name for pinning or disambiguation
‘path’             all except remote archives   Path to the registry data (flake input ‘.outPath’)
‘core-src’         ‘elpa’                       Path to Emacs source tree for building Core ELPA packages
‘auto-sync-only’   ‘elpa’                       If ‘true’, skip packages that cannot be built from source
‘base-url’         ‘archive-contents’           Base URL from which to download package tarballs


