7.1 Package not found after editing init.el
===========================================

If Twist cannot find a package you just added, run the lock command to
update the lock files:

     nix run .#lock

   Every new package must be locked before it can be built in pure mode.


File: emacs-twist.info,  Node: Rate-limited by GitHub,  Next: Build failure on a specific package,  Prev: Package not found after editing initel,  Up: Troubleshooting

7.2 Rate-limited by GitHub
==========================

See *note Add an access token to GitHub:: above for instructions on
adding a GitHub access token to ‘nix.conf’.


File: emacs-twist.info,  Node: Build failure on a specific package,  Prev: Rate-limited by GitHub,  Up: Troubleshooting

7.3 Build failure on a specific package
=======================================

Use ‘nix eval’ to inspect the package metadata:

     nix eval .#emacs.packageInputs.<package-name>

   You can also check reverse dependencies:

     nix eval .#emacs.revDeps.<package-name>


